                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.51 Et 3/15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bading</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-01T12:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1923—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 10:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. Your 17, November 6, 3 p.m. In view of the general opinion that the loan will
                    be a failure and that the final contract will not be signed, I have not thought
                    it desirable to bring the matter to the President’s attention unless again
                    instructed to do so by the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bading</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
